      "text": "A 30-year-old woman presents with excessive bleeding following a tooth extraction. She reports a history of recurrent nosebleeds and easy bruising since childhood. Lab tests show prolonged activated partial thromboplastin time (aPTT) and normal prothrombin time (PT). Further testing reveals decreased levels of a clotting factor\u2019s activity. Which of the following is not an intrinsic factor?",
